# TypeScript and React Quality

Use clear, maintainable TypeScript and React patterns.

- Prefer explicit types at module boundaries and public APIs.
- Use early returns to reduce nesting and keep control flow readable.
- Keep components and functions small; extract helpers only when reuse or clarity improves.
- Name handlers with `handle*` when they respond to events.
- Prefer immutable updates and predictable data flow.
- Avoid adding comments for obvious code; add concise comments only for non-obvious logic.
